            <div id="subtitle"><h1>Ongoing Sailboat Replacement Campaigns</h1></div>


            <p>The BHS Sailing Team's competition sailboats presently consist of two fleets: a primary fleet eight Flying Juniors (FJs), and a secondary fleet of six Vanguard 15s (V15s). With a typical team size often in excess of 25 sailors, all these boats are in use nearly every day during the competition season.</p>
            <p>The Friends of Bainbridge Island High School Sailing has entered into a Memorandum of Agreement with the Bainbridge Island Metro Park and Recreation District. Pursuant to this MOA, the Park District owns the competition sailboats (as well as the other support and sailing venue assets). In return for use of these boats in training and competition, as well as many other benefits, the Friends of BIHSS helps raise funds for sailboat acquisition. Once purchased, the sailboats are then shared between Team use during the competition season and use by double-handed training classes and clinics in the BIMPRD's Community Sailing Program.</p>
            <p>The Friends of BIHSS has adopted a Long-Term Business Plan for Fundraising for Sailboat Acquisition ( <a href="http://bhssailing.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/FBIHSS.boat_.acquisition.business.plan_.4-15.pdf">Boat Aqcuisition Business Plan</a>  ) that governs replacement of these two fleets. The fundraising campaigns are distinct from one another, and they run simultaneously and in parallel.</p>
            <p>The primary fleet was replaced in 2014; the secondary fleet will be the next to be replaced. As further described below, the present secondary fleet of V15s will be replaced with Z420 sailboats. Each fleet is on a six-year replacement schedule; the culmination points are staggered so that a new primary or secondary fleet is delivered every three years. The next fleet replacement is projected for delivery in time for the spring 2017 season.</p>
